From ce2532b8ecafa0c6b6a71506c7b68310a3564c61 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: GeorgeWilliam1999 <George.W.Scriven@gmail.com>
Date: Sun, 10 May 2026 15:13:52 +0200
Subject: [PATCH] Kalman: add NRKExtrapolator skeleton with Catch2 unit tests

Adds a header-only Extrapolators::NRKExtrapolator struct in device/kalman/ParKalman/include/, mirroring the surface API of the existing RungeKuttaNystromExtrapolator but taking the magnetic-field vector as a direct argument (float3 B) instead of a MagneticField::Magfield grid. The body is a faithful restatement of RKN::make_fast_step and is numerically equivalent under identical inputs.

No algorithm wrapper, no sequence wiring, no property hooks, no weights. The header is unreachable from any current Allen sequence and therefore cannot affect throughput or physics performance.

Five Catch2 v3 unit tests register under tag [NRKExtrapolator] via the existing catch_discover_tests glob: zero-field straight line, sign symmetry, qop invariance, qop linearity at small step, and zero-step idempotency. unit_tests now links WrapperInterface so the ParKalman headers are visible.

Local CI dry-run: lb-check-copyright master and lb-format -n on staged files both pass. Full build and ctest deferred to push.

Signed-off-by: GeorgeWilliam1999 <George.W.Scriven@gmail.com>
---
 .../ParKalman/include/NRKExtrapolator.cuh     |  99 ++++++++++++
 .../include/NRKExtrapolatorConstants.cuh      |  23 +++
 test/unit_tests/CMakeLists.txt                |   2 +-
 .../generic/src/TestNRKExtrapolator.cu        | 149 ++++++++++++++++++
 4 files changed, 272 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)
 create mode 100644 device/kalman/ParKalman/include/NRKExtrapolator.cuh
 create mode 100644 device/kalman/ParKalman/include/NRKExtrapolatorConstants.cuh
